<head>
  <title>High-Profile Athlete Injury Report</title>
</head>
<body>
  <outline text="Athletics (Track &amp; Field)">
    <outline text="Gout Gout — Grade-three left hamstring tear suffered in training in Brisbane (2026-07-09)" type="link" url="https://www.olympics.com/en/news/gout-gout-injury-hamstring-world-athletics-under-20-championships" description="Removes the U20 200m world record holder from an anticipated showdown with American Tate Taylor at the World U20 Championships"/>
  </outline>
  <outline text="Baseball">
    <outline text="Marco Raya — Right shoulder impingement (2026-07-08)" type="link" url="https://www.mlb.com/news/twins-injuries-and-roster-moves" description="Twins lose a pitching option for at least 15 days"/>
    <outline text="Endy Rodriguez — Left glute strain (2026-07-08)" type="link" url="https://www.mlbtraderumors.com/2026/07/pirates-to-place-endy-rodriguez-on-injured-list.html" description="Pirates lose their starting catcher for at least 10 days"/>
    <outline text="Giancarlo Stanton — Right calf strain (originally suffered running the bases on April 24 vs. the Astros); recent rehab setback after re-aggravating the calf during a running progression (2026-07-07)" type="link" url="https://lastwordonsports.com/baseball/2026/07/07/nyy-stanton-injury-update/" description="Yankees continue without their veteran slugger amid an offense that has struggled with injuries; manager Aaron Boone still expects him back at some point in 2026"/>
    <outline text="Byron Buxton — Aggravated hip injury while being caught stealing in the 1st inning vs. Yankees (2026-07-05)" type="link" url="https://www.yardbarker.com/mlb/articles/2026_injury_report_updates_on_buxton_suarez_chisholm_jr/s1_17653_44031703" description="Twins lose their 2026 All-Star outfielder from the lineup for an undetermined stretch"/>
    <outline text="Jazz Chisholm Jr. — Right toe discomfort, noticed jogging gingerly to first base after a fly out (2026-07-05)" type="link" url="https://www.yardbarker.com/mlb/articles/2026_injury_report_updates_on_buxton_suarez_chisholm_jr/s1_17653_44031703" description="Risk of losing Yankees' starting second baseman if it worsens"/>
    <outline text="Ranger Suarez — Left adductor tightness, pulled early from start vs. Angels (2026-07-05)" type="link" url="https://www.yardbarker.com/mlb/articles/2026_injury_report_updates_on_buxton_suarez_chisholm_jr/s1_17653_44031703" description="Phillies could lose their 2026 AL All-Star-caliber starter from the rotation"/>
    <outline text="Brandon Woodruff — Right shoulder inflammation (2026-07-05)" type="link" url="https://www.covers.com/sport/baseball/mlb/injuries" description="Brewers rotation loses a top starter for at least two full turns"/>
    <outline text="Triston Casas — Torn right patellar tendon (out since May); recently shut down from hitting progression (2026-07-05)" type="link" url="https://www.yardbarker.com/mlb/articles/2026_injury_report_updates_on_buxton_suarez_chisholm_jr/s1_17653_44031703" description="Red Sox lose starting first baseman for the remainder of the 2026 season"/>
    <outline text="Corey Seager — Recurrence of lower back inflammation; his third injured list stint of the 2026 season (previously missed time with the same back issue and with a concussion) (2026-07-01)" type="link" url="https://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/49238350/rangers-corey-seager-back-il-lower-back-inflammation" description="Rangers lose their star shortstop again, continuing a season of infield instability; Josh Smith recalled from Triple-A as replacement"/>
    <outline text="Brent Rooker — Cartilage tear in left knee, discovered during an examination at Stanford; requires season-ending surgery (2026-07-01)" type="link" url="https://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/49244022/a-slugger-brent-rooker-season-ending-left-knee-surgery" description="Athletics lose their two-time All-Star middle-of-the-order bat for the remainder of the 2026 season"/>
  </outline>
  <outline text="Basketball">
    <outline text="Aliyah Boston — Lower right leg injury (2026-07-08)" type="link" url="https://athlonsports.com/wnba/indiana-fever/indiana-fever-announce-aliyah-boston-injury-update-la-sparks-game" description="Fever forced to manage the availability of both Boston and Caitlin Clark during a back-to-back stretch; Boston, a voted-in 2026 All-Star starter, is having a career-best scoring season (17.1 ppg on 50.4% shooting) and was in danger of missing her first game since May 17"/>
    <outline text="Jalen Brunson — Surgery to repair a left wrist injury that he played through during the Knicks' championship playoff run (2026-07-07)" type="link" url="https://sports.yahoo.com/nba/breaking-news/article/knicks-superstar-jalen-brunson-undergoes-left-wrist-surgery-expected-to-be-ready-for-2026-27-nba-season-155927234.html" description="Reigning Finals MVP and starting point guard sidelined for part of the offseason program, though expected back for training camp"/>
    <outline text="A'ja Wilson — Foot injury sustained in a game against the Chicago Sky (2026-07-06)" type="link" url="https://www.nwaonline.com/news/2026/jul/07/injuries-taking-toll-throughout-wnba/" description="Aces without their All-Star forward/center for a short stretch, including a loss to Indiana"/>
